Here’s to 2023🥂

2023 here we come! 

Some fun music updates 

I’m going be releasing some new songs soon which will be part of an upcoming album that will be coming out later this Summer. 

My partner in crime @davewoodmusic and I are finally going to be sharing some of the awesome new music that our incredible artists at @xiximusicpro have been hard at work on.

#dowhatyoulove

Pretty awesome news. I’ve been honored to know this amazingly talented human being @davewoodmusic that I get to call family for 20 years and we officially made it official with @xiximusicpro 

After so many gigs/rehearsals/live recordings/music videos/bottles of scotch/cups of expensive coffee/writing sessions/and being part of helping launch some pretty rad careers we felt like it was about time. I can’t think of anyone else I’d rather be making art with. 🥃✨🥃 man, these pics/vids are from the archive and I couldnt squeeze them all in lol

Follow us at @xiximusicpro for all updates and to follow the incredibly talented artists who have given us their trust and who we’ve been so fortunate to be part of their artistic journey!

@baywud and I wanted to release a song that inspires hope.  With all that’s going on in the world at the moment we wanted to share something that might be a reminder to check in on your friends and family. It’s about being there for those people who are your chosen family.  For all those rare people who ask how you are and then wait to hear the answer and who lift you up and love you for the imperfect person that you are. Who will help shine light on dark days and give you strength when you are without. 

Written by me, Michael Baywud, and Rune Westberg

This holiday season marks the 3rd since my grandmothers passing. I been feeling her presence a lot lately and it’s only amplified during the holidays when my parents get to visit and we all get to spend this wonderful time together as a family. 

I wrote and produced this song weeks after she passed to a poem that she had written titled “Somehow.” She wrote from her perspective about how she hopes for it to still be possible to BE here after she goes.  Her words are a wish to still be present after her passing.  I wanted to sing her words back to her  so that I might be able to tell her that she very much is. Her verses allowed me to write a chorus from my perspective back to her.  Best co-write I’ve ever had ❤️ I inherited my grandfather’s (her husband’s) accordion which I play on this and I think it’s the first time it’s been played since his passing 40 years ago.  She was always into butterflies. I’ve been seeing many of them lately, especially in our backyard. They come pay me a visit, stay a while, make me feel safe and loved.  I truly believe the connections we have with those we love so much and cherish don’t end, they just change shape. I love you, Momma and know you’re still here with us here somehow someway. 

Link in my profile to the video and to see her beautiful handwritten poem 🦋
